				<td colspan="2"><span>GD, im in my 30s aoe kiting.  I started out with 1 or 2 wolves by the time they stopped being darkblue  i was pulling herds of wolves at a time usually 10 to 15.  Usually i would only get hurt when someone thought me runnin in circles around 15 wolves was me needing help and they would aoe or start rooting wolves, and suddenly wolves that couldnt hit me running could once they were rooted.  
<br />

<br />
A druid did that to me and I went from 97 health to 3% in less than 2 seconds.  I got out in a wide circle kept selos and hymn running till i hit 30% tightened my circle back into aoe range and proceeded to aoe/chant them out. When all was done there were 15 dead wolves and me at 32% health and the druid going &quot;omg that was awsome, im so sorry i almost killed you =p&quot;. Every time i solo somewhere new, group somewhere new, I learn so much more of just how incredibly flexible and effective a Bard is.  It has been a truly humbling experience, but undeniably fun.
<br />
 
<br />

<br />
Most druids i have met with Braull are super nice, have met more than one ranger that took exception to me swarm kiting and one particular bard.  One ranger in GD tried to train me with giants and wolves during my kite, took me a minute to get it under control and get them all down.  Well that really mad him mad because then this dummy starts /ooc'n what he has done and how Bards shouldnt be kiting (/boggle). The rest of the zone chews his tush off and he disappears for a bit then shows up on the edge of one my swarms.  I was ready for him this time though. I had agro pulled the whole train and was running wide out view looking out for him, he sat off throwing DDs roots and snares at my kite trying i guess in his mind to ks, screw up , whatever,<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-12.gif" border="0" alt="Mad" hspace="2" />. I waited till two of the ones he snared made it to him. Then i aimed the cat his direction and took him the rest.  It seems the pack liked him better than me.  He made it out of the mass and ran for zone...............albeit looking rather scraggly.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" />
<br />

