				<td colspan="2"><span>i've been kiting HGs in Rathe for a long time now. I was in Rathe one day/night, this event happened at about 4am CST. I had been the only person in zone for about 4 hours. So, i was charming and kiting, and pulling all 12 HG spawn spots.
<br />
I would look to see if anyone else was in zone after killing each kite and before pulling the next.
<br />
I checked, no-one there but me, so i start pulling all the HGs as they PoP, after awhile, i have 12 HGs chasing me, I lead them to my favorite kiting hole (where i run the rim of the hole and keep all the HGs in the bottom of the hole). 
<br />

<br />
When i kite i have an AFK message that says i'm kiting multiple mobs and can't answer or i'll die. I watched this guy log in and appear close to where i was kiting, and with in 30 seconds get a rude tell about me hoarding all the mobs. My afk message was returned to him. This guy (druid or ranger, couldn't tell) then proceeds to snare one of the HGs and run into my swarm of MOBs and starts attacking the one he slowed. Since i was chant kiting, i had minimal aggro on all but my current target. Yep, you guessed it, the othe r 8-9 HGs proceeded to pummel the snot out of him.
<br />

<br />
i get more tells from him saying i trained him and he was going to report me to a GM. Since GMs are hardly ever on i never returned a tell to him, just let my afk message flash back at him.
<br />

<br />
about 15 minutes later, i have a GM standing there watching me as i'm finishing of my second round of kiting. After i explained everything to the GM,all was cool. I guess that jerk learned ya don't mess with a bards kiting.
